Bring a large #saucepan{} of water to the boil with @salt{1/4%tsp} for the noodles.
Halve the @bell pepper{1}(halved and sliced into thin strips) and discard the core and seeds.
Trim and halve the @green beans{80%g}(trimmed and halved).
Peel and grate the @garlic{2%cloves}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}).

Heat a drizzle of @oil{drizzle} in a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat.
Once the oil is hot, add the @British beef mince{240%g} and sliced pepper. Stir-fry until the mince has browned and the pepper has softened, ~{5-6%minutes}.
Use a #spoon{} to break up the mince as it cooks, then drain and discard any excess fat.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw mince.

Meanwhile, add the @egg noodle nest{2} and green beans to the pan of boiling water. Cook until tender, ~{4%minutes}.
Once cooked, drain in a #colander{}.

> TIP: Run the noodles under cold water to stop them sticking together and to keep the beans vibrant.

Once the beef mince has browned and the pepper has started to soften, add the garlic and stir-fry for ~{1%minute}.

Once cooked, add the noodles and beans to the frying pan.
Pour in the @hoisin sauce{96%g}, @ketjap manis{25%g}, @soy sauce{15%g} and @water{50%g} for the sauce, then mix well to combine.
Cook until everything's piping hot, ~{2-3%minutes}, then remove from the heat.

> IMPORTANT: The mince is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Share the hoisin beef noodles between your #serving bowls{}.
Finish with a sprinkling of @roasted white sesame seeds{5%g} for those who'd like them.
Enjoy!